Job Title: Senior Joint Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations (JEMSO) Naval Aviation Analyst

Work Location: Nellis AFB, Nevada

Clearance: Current/active TS+

Please note that you must be a US citizen to apply to the job posting

Education: HS Diploma with twelve (12) plus years of related experience

Schedule: Monday - Friday day shift

Travel: Occasional

Salary: Commensurate with experience

Job Listing Number: 23-003/NV22023

LCAT: Sr Naval Aviation Analyst


Overview: S4 Inc. employees selected for this position will be supporting USSTRATCOM JEMSOC missions in order to provide the JEMSOC Director with Planning, Analysis, Spectrum Management, and Intelligence support. In addition, S4 employees will support Advisory and Assistance Services (A&AS) for JCER to accomplish Joint Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations (JEMSO) readiness evaluations in order to accredit each Service/United States Special Operations Command (USSOCOM).


Specific Duties: In this position, you will be responsible for:

Developing detailed mission analysis and integrating resources to determine capabilities to meet the JCER mission;
Making recommendations to service or joint tactics, weapon schools, or publications based on findings of JCER evaluations;
Analyzing threat data and controlling receipt and dissemination of foreign intelligence information;
Evaluating emerging EMSO threats in order to present findings, conclusions, and recommendations based on evaluation results;
Conducting tactical, operational, and strategic level research concerning the impact of existing and emerging EMSO threats to joint operations;


Qualifications:

Twelve (12) plus years of Operational level experience with preference to candidates with higher level broadening assignments such as Joint, CCMD and Service level staff;
Understanding of current service capabilities to include communication/tactical data links and tactics with knowledge of vulnerabilities in the presence of threat EMSO
Experience conducting studies, performing research, reporting, and making recommendations concerning instrumentation and evaluation resources necessary to execute risk reduction and evaluation events ensuring the coordination of communications, logistics, materiel, data collection and personnel training, issue and alternative definitions, and personnel requirements for each designated activity;


Desired Qualifications:

Bachelor's degree or higher with more than fifteen (15) years in Naval Aviation desired
Preferably expertise specializing in fighter/attack combat aircraft; however, experience in other armed aviation platforms is acceptable;
Preferably experience working with partnering agencies that share interests in support of data collection, reduction, or JEMSO operations in conjunction with JCER evaluations;
Training and certification as a PMP are highly recommended for individuals lacking requisite military leadership experience.

