Job Title: Joint Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations (JEMSO) Sr. Analyst Operations Research

Work Location: Nellis AFB, Nevada

Clearance: Current/active TS+

Please note that you must be a US citizen to apply to the job posting

Education: Bachelor's degree in a technical field such as mathematics, physics, engineering, or operational research with 12 plus years of related operational experience

Schedule: Monday - Friday day shift

Travel: Occasional

Salary: Commensurate with experience

Job Listing Number: NV23012

LCAT: JEMSO Sr ORSA Analyst


Overview: S4 Inc. employees selected for this position will be supporting USSTRATCOM JEMSOC missions in order to provide the JEMSOC Director with Planning, Analysis, Spectrum Management, and Intelligence support. In addition, S4 employees will support Advisory and Assistance Services (A&AS) for JCER to accomplish Joint Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations (JEMSO) readiness evaluations in order to accredit each Service/United States Special Operations Command (USSOCOM).


Specific Duties: In this position, you will be responsible for:

Making recommendations to service or joint tactics, weapon schools, or publications based on findings of JCER evaluations;
Analyzing threat data and controlling receipt and dissemination of foreign intelligence information;
Evaluating emerging EW threats in order to present findings, conclusions, and recommendations based on evaluation results;
Conducting tactical, operational, and strategic level research concerning the impact of existing and emerging EMSO threats to joint operations;
Performing EMSO evaluation planning, analysis, and report writing;
Performing scientific work requiring design, development, and adaptation of mathematical statistical models and other scientific methods and techniques with current, usable knowledge of mathematical and statistical software package such as: JMP, SAS, EXCEL, MATLAB;
Working with SMEs, Analysts, and Military to define data requirements for data collection purposes and maximize the opportunity for statistically significant results;
Validating the effectiveness of data collection for post-event analysis
Serving as lead author for the analysis portion of evaluation plans and reports;
Identifying requirements for specialized data analysis software and other tools;
Conducting analysis, research, and studies to identify evaluation objectives and recommend alternative courses of action;
Developing detailed data collection and data analysis plans to explicitly state how JCER will collect, manage, store, control, and analyze data for each evaluation event, maximizing use of existing data management tools and assisting with new database designs and data extraction;
Performing detailed analysis of EMSO objectives tied to Universal Joint Tasks (UJTs) or Mission Essential Tasks (METs), Measures of Effectiveness (MOE), and Measures of Performance (MOP) to conduct research utilizing all available sources of classified and unclassified information and assess JEMSO readiness metrics;
Analyzing collected evaluation data and reporting analysis results as requested in various forms to include tables, graphs, and figures

Qualifications:

Bachelor's degree in a technical field such as mathematics, physics, engineering, or operational research
12+ years of relevant operational experience
Familiarity with modern data analysis and visualization tools and programming languages such as Python, R, Tableau, Databricks, Plotly, Envision, etc.;
Understanding of current service capabilities and tactics with knowledge of vulnerabilities in the presence of threat EW


